{
  "conceptual": "\n<p sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"3\">This component forwards any message that it receives to the active <a href=\"~/pages/docs/runtime/application/game-state.md\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"3\">game state</a>.</p>\n<p sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"5\">Game states can have <a href=\"~/pages/docs/runtime/world/world-messaging.md\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"5\">message handlers</a> just like any other reflected type.\nHowever, since they are not part of the <a href=\"~/pages/docs/runtime/world/worlds.md\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"6\">world</a>, messages are not delivered to them. By attaching this component to a game object, all event messages that arrive here are forwarded to the active game state.</p>\n<p sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"8\">This way, a game state can receive information, such as when a trigger gets activated. Multiple of these components can exist in a scene, gathering and forwarding messages from many different game objects, so that the game state can react to all of them.</p>\n<h2 id=\"see-also\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"10\">See Also</h2>\n<ul sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"12\">\n<li sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"12\"><a href=\"~/pages/docs/runtime/application/game-state.md\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"12\">Game States</a></li>\n<li sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"13\"><a href=\"~/pages/docs/runtime/world/world-messaging.md\" sourcefile=\"pages/docs/custom-code/game-logic/forward-events-to-game-state-component.md\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"13\">Messaging</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
